@MiyuMinちゃん Hey I'm not one to criticize liking something different for the sake of it being different, but you still got to accept most people find it painful and ugly. If thats a cross they want to bear then more power to them but you got to accept that comes with the price of most people hating it.

Same for genres.

Problem comes when none of this at all is baked into Marathon, its a weird left turn the devs decided to make on their own while they wear an old IP like a skinsuit. No ones gonna be a fan of this.

@realvibingrn marathon DOES have an audience, it has MANY people that love it, its just not your type of game, but that doesent give you the right to delete us from existence, 50 to 90k players IS an audience

its niche yes but that doesent mean its bad and it doesent mean we dont exist it just means not everyone likes this type of game and that is NORMAL

but instead of acting like an adult should and leaving the community alone instead of hating on them, people are farming this stupid drama to make money with youtube videos and making more people hate on us

@MiyuMinちゃん Yeah, if it was an indie or AA game, then it would be fine to be niche. It's not. It's a AAA title, dude. 4 years of development. 850 person studio.
Do the math. No, go on. Then start considering how much you and its audience need to pay for it.
Don't let me stop you, though.

@MiyuMinちゃん Dude, people can say whatever they like about that game. Like point out that it's made by art thieves.
It's up to YOU to show how awesome, funny or friendly your fanbase is, thus making people want to join it.
And man, you're failing that like it was a professional sport and you were a promising young talent.
